@manuman also known as Manichan Landry, stands as a distinguished DJ producer and event promoter based in Montreal, Canada. As the visionary founder and owner of the Groove & Bass Festival, a psychedelic electronic music and arts festival in Quebec, Canada, Manüman has cultivated a dynamic platform for the convergence of global talents and artistic expressions.

Introduced to the realm of electronic music and DJ culture in 2009, Manüman embarked on his journey behind the decks at the tender age of 14. His passion for the music and the scene has since burgeoned, taking him on an international exploration of diverse music landscapes. It was during his sojourn in Europe, immersed in their techno scene, that he recognized the optimal medium to channel his fervor – as a DJ. Thus, the inception of his project, Manüman.

With a seasoned career, Manüman has graced dance floors across Europe and North America, delivering captivating performances from Switzerland to the USA to Mexico and beyond. Sharing event line-ups with renowned international talents such as Kenny Glasgow, Khainz, Alex Stein, Marten Horger, Perfect Stranger, Fernanda Pistelli, Beth Lydi, Gene Farris, Jacidorex, gaga & mateo, D-nox, and others, he has become a fixture in the global electronic music circuit.

Rooted in diverse musical influences spanning the entire house and techno spectrum, Manüman draws inspiration from his immersive experiences in Germany and Brazil. Navigating through crisp percussion hooks and groovy basslines, his musical journey weaves a tapestry of underground tech grooves, creating an immersive vibe that is bound to captivate both body and soul.

track.description:
This week on the RIPEcast, Space Cowboys welcome back Smoove to the Bay Area. 

Aloha Funkateers 

Back in Y2K era San Francisco, there was a trend amongst the uber cool restaurants where  - as part of the dining room ambience - you would often find a DJ mixing live during dinner service. It was here, spinning vinyl all night propped up at the end of the bar, in this bastion of late 20th century California fusion cuisine I found my entrance into the fantastical wonderland that is the Bay Area DJ community. And it was here where I first encountered the Space Cowboys. 

The subsequent years featured a significant increase of the color orange into my wardrobe, Halloween undergrounds, a Unimog, breakbeats (so. Many. Breakz!) renegades in Golden Gate Park, that thing in the desert, decompression/recompression, Love parades, rhinestones, Martha, NewsBreakz, heartbreakz.  And yes, a New Year’s Day sunrise party. 

It was a glorious time to be alive 

So I think it’s fitting my first time back at BOC in *this many* years was the 25th anniversary.  I was hella psyched to be on this years line up because, if I’m being perfectly honest, I have missed you all. Spinning this set was a true joy and it was an honor to be back with the original crew. 

-Smoove
track.title: RIPEcast Smoove - Breakfast of Champions '25

Hour two was the second guest mix appearance from my good Danish friend and boss of Discoholics Anonymous Recordings, Ken Avalon - AKA Discoholic Ken. Greg and I were unable to host this week, so Even Funkier stepped in for a live broadcast of fabulously eclectic grooves. Top quality tunes as always, with a tropical summer vibe to chase those clouds away. He hosts his own show on NDC Radio called "Funkier Sounds", as well as promoting a mixtape series called "Funkier Sessions". Get in touch if you are a DJ with a funky vibe to share! 

https://soundcloud.com/evenfunkier

This week's guest was Timewarp Inc, aka Angelos Stoumpos, a Greek DJ, producer, and label owner. His music blends funk, breaks, nu-disco, freestyle, and dub, and his tracks have been featured in major international compilations, including Black Coffee, Sensuality Lounge, and Ibiza Global Radio Moods. He has also performed at renowned festivals such as Spring Three (Vienna), San Pelegrino (Croatia), and Tibe Festival (Brazil). His DJ sets have taken him to clubs across Europe, including Austria, Germany, Switzerland, and Brazil.

Timewarp Inc’s talent has been praised by industry figures such as Craig Charles (BBC), Parov Stelar, and Fort Knox Five. In 2004, he launched his independent label, Timewarp Music, which has released hundreds of digital tracks, albums, and compilations from over 100 artists worldwide. In 2009, he founded Kraak Records, an electronic music label. With over 25 years of experience, Timewarp Inc is also a sound and mastering engineer, licensing music for major ad campaigns. His dedication to high-quality music and his ability to evolve with the industry make him a key figure in modern funk and electronic music.

Originally from Ireland Blamhaus is now based in London, UK. As a teen he got into electronic music from legends such as daft punk, the prodigy, leftfield being major influences but as he dug deeper discovering artists such as Mad Mike, Drexciya, Claude young, Mark Broom, Jeff Mill cemented his love for the underground. He runs three labels B-Haus, Echtraí both focusing on Techno/House and Wołno (a pun for the Polish word for “Slowly”) based around slower tempos with a focus on cross genre productions.

Una vez más ya veis que apostamos por el producto nacional y emergente, no tenemos ninguna duda de que nuestro participante número 72 va a llegar bien lejos y con el apoyo de vosotros seguro que lo consigue. https://soundcloud.com/chris-nexus-6 es un veterano de la escena electro que comenzó su andadura musical en 1995 (Francia). En sus inicios, se centró en el sonido Old School Rave, finalmente entro en la secta del Electro.

Su pasión por la música también lo llevo a escribir numerosas críticas en Electro Alliance y Electric Kingdom (R.I.P. Santino) consolidándose como una voz reconocida dentro de la comunidad electro.

Como diseñador, Chris ha colaborado con sellos como New Flesh Records, Rave Or Die, Zodiak Commune, Shipwrec y Fundamental Bass Intelligence. 

Además, es el responsable del programa Sound Chemistry.

Der Energieberater - Vinyl-DJ, Remixer, Producer,
Ganz nach dem Motto "always surprise the audience" legt er bereits seit Jahren in Clubs und auf Events auf - in Wiesbaden früher in der Pudelbar und im Gestüt Renz. Als Resident der "Sex and the City-Party Tour“ von Pro Sieben rockte er deutschlandweit in den größten Clubs. Derzeit ist er im Schick im Rahmen des „SingleKlubs" als 7“-Vinyl-DJ und mit 12“-House-Scheiben unter dem Motto „Timeless“ aktiv. In seinem 50-Minuten Crazy-Mashup-Mix hört ihr alles was in die Beine geht. Von Funk über Oldschool-Hip-Hop, Mashups, Disco bis Filmmusik…. Volle 7inch- Energie!

Nebenbei dem DJing produziert er - eigene Tracks und Remixes befreundeter Bands und Songwriter -  vor allem Indietronic und Alternative-Clubsounds. In den letzten Jahren bearbeitete er viele Bands, vor allem aus der Rhein-Main-Region: darunter Wyoming, Dynarchy, Louis Peschke, Velveteen, Citizen Tim, Rupert Falsch, Scut, Janis Elko und Gisbert zu Knyphausen.
